# 9. Why This Works

At every index of `a`, exactly one of the following must happen:

* It is skipped (equivalent to inserting a `0` in `b`).
* It is paired with the current element of `b`.

These two choices cover every valid alignment while preserving the order of elements. Since each state `(i, j)` is solved only once, the DP explores all possibilities efficiently and guarantees the optimal answer.

